# Projection: PURRDF → pure schema-org. GENERATED by `purrdf regenerate` (mappings) from mapping-dsl/ — DO NOT EDIT.
# Lossy and directional by design; drops: PURRDF AccessibilityFacet individuals are emitted as IRIs; schema.org expects specific text tokens (wheelchairAccessible, stepFreeAccess, etc.). The consumer must map IRIs to tokens.; PURRDF AccessibilityFacet individuals are emitted as IRIs; schema.org expects specific text tokens (flashingHazard, motionSimulationHazard, soundHazard, etc.). The consumer must map IRIs to tokens.; schema.org has no plan/execution de-conflation; the Execution is projected as a flat Action; the postal reference frame (axes, topological kind, metric) is dropped; only the flat schema:PostalAddress component values survive; membership period, role, and standpoint drop; the flat affiliation edge survives; the inverse reading: the organization gains schema:alumni pointing at each alumnus; the Participation's period / confidence / evidence / standpoint collapse to a flat schema:attendee edge; Glottocodes excluded; only 2-3 letter primary subtags; the birth Participation (role, period, confidence, standpoint) and fuzzy-date bounds are dropped; only the principal's birth instant survives as schema:birthDate; the birth Participation detail drops; only the principal's birthplace survives; the open posting-kind value collapses to schema's fixed BlogPosting class; provenance and confidence of the capture-time claim are dropped; the criterion/rubric structure and scale metadata collapse to a bare ratingValue; each review stays authored by its vantage — N competing assessments emit N coexisting ClaimReviews, never one aggregated rating (P9); the affordance's editorial name/label is site UI copy and is NOT fabricated; only the structural CommunicateAction + mailto: target derive; the affordance's editorial name is site UI copy and is NOT fabricated; only the structural CommunicateAction + tel: target derive; the first-class ContactPointType value collapses to its label string; the CoordinateObservation relator (vantage, confidence, reference frame, temporal scope) collapses to a flat schema:geo edge; non-displayable/superseded observations are suppressed; the Copyright relator (year, notice, status) collapses to a flat schema:copyrightHolder edge; the structured Copyright relator (holder, year, status) collapses to a flat schema:copyrightNotice edge; the Copyright relator (holder, notice, status) collapses to a flat schema:copyrightYear edge; the Skill/Occupation distinction in credentialFor collapses to schema:competencyRequired; the issuer organization relator collapses to a flat schema:recognizedBy edge; the currency reference frame collapses to its ISO 4217 / ticker code; schema:currenciesAccepted is a free-text code list; the member document is REUSED as the schema:DataDownload node; its PURRDF typing drops; the feed's ordered membership flattens to schema:dataFeedElement; each member is REUSED as a schema:DataFeedItem (no item-wrapper mint); the death Participation (role, period, confidence, standpoint) is dropped; only the principal's death instant survives; the death Participation detail drops; only the principal's deathplace survives; the subOrganizationOf hierarchy and any contested succession/standpoint claims collapse to a flat schema:department edge; depiction context, audience, period, and authority dropped; only the depicted entity survives; description withheld when entity is not explicitly eligible for consumerPublicSite; the destruction event's place, participants, and standpoint are dropped; only the instant survives as schema:dissolutionDate; authority provenance, confidence, standpoint, and exact-vs-close match distinction collapse to a schema.org identity URL; skos:closeMatch authority links are not emitted; none for the tag triple — propertyID/value/name carry the full EXIF tag; the purrdf:ExifTag node is reused as the PropertyValue; the creation event's place, participants, and standpoint are dropped; only the instant survives as schema:foundingDate; the uncertainty band (purrdf:latestEnd) and the purrdf:temporalPrecision qualifier are dropped; only the earliest bound survives as a single schema:startDate; orientation + sexAssignedAtBirth dropped; sex/gender conflated; modality, veridicality, confidence, standpoint poset, and the reified statement content dropped; verdicts ride as per-review ClaimReview nodes (mapSchemaClaimReview) preserving the data's epistemic shape — attributed stays authored, anonymous stays anonymous, nothing computed; appearance only when the evidence spine is complete; the specialized PURRDF whole-to-part subproperty, if any, is collapsed to generic schema:hasPart; the siteType distinction (headquarters/branch/registered) is dropped; the target node's own Place projection preserves geographic detail; tag IRI lost; only label text emitted; displayable false tags suppressed; the article's title doubles as its headline (schema.org's article idiom); jurisdiction and any standpoint/validity detail on the record drop; schema's PropertyValue carries only the scheme/value/url/name quad; the record's rdfs:label is its display name; the depiction's context/period/audience drop; the entity gains schema:image pointing at the depicting MediaObject; unit (pixels) is implicit in schema:height when emitted as integer; MediaObject also covers audio and video; the ImageObject projection is lossy for non-image media; unit (pixels) is implicit in schema:width when emitted as integer; the first-class purrdf:Language collapses to its BCP-47 / ISO 639-1 tag string; script and variety detail drop; only ISIC-V4-scheme classifications are emitted; NAICS and other schemes are dropped; only NAICS-scheme classifications are emitted; ISIC and other schemes are dropped; the code is emitted as a plain literal; contribution period, provenance, confidence drop; the Membership relator (organization, period, role, confidence, standpoint) collapses to a flat schema:jobTitle literal; contested membership claims are not distinguished; CEFR/ILR/ACTFL level and skill modality dropped; only LEI-scheme identifiers are emitted; other schemes (ROR, company registration, Wikidata) are dropped in this projection; the location's type distinction (Place vs VirtualLocation vs StorageLocation) is preserved by the target node's own rdf:type projection, but the locatedAt relation itself loses the structural subproperty (storedIn, physicalPlace); contribution period, provenance, confidence, degree drop; the Capacity relator (provenance, unit, temporal scope, standpoint) collapses to a flat schema:maximumAttendeeCapacity integer; non-displayable/superseded capacities are suppressed; restricted to purrdf:Place to avoid projecting byte capacities from StorageLocation; microblog narrows to schema's SocialMediaPosting (no microblog subclass); provider (string, no faithful Organization node), context window, and training cutoff dropped; the card/agent distinction collapses onto the agent; the event's open kind value, temporal fuzziness and participation detail drop; only the action shape with its origin survives; the event's open kind value, temporal fuzziness and participation detail drop; only the action shape with its destination survives; the WEMI spine collapses; track-level frame-relative content and declared losses are lost; recording event provenance, take/overdub structure, and standpoint-indexed performance claims collapse to a flat schema:MusicRecording; the WEMI spine collapses: Work, Expression, and Manifestation are flattened into one schema:MusicComposition; realization mode and notation frame are lost; non-displayable names (deadnames) dropped; the NetworkAddress frame, type, provenance, and standpoint are dropped; only the URL string survives; standpoint, confidence, temporal scope, suppression state, aboutness, tagging dropped; Comment-specific typing collapsed to schema:NoteDigitalDocument (rdflib UNION limit); the Occupancy relator (provenance, unit, temporal scope, standpoint) collapses to a flat schema:occupancy integer; non-displayable/superseded occupancies are suppressed; restricted to purrdf:Place to avoid projecting byte occupancies from StorageLocation; the offering is REUSED as the schema:Offer node; price/availability detail is not modelled; the spec is REUSED as schema:OpeningHoursSpecification; price/validity detail is not modelled; the Participation's period / confidence / evidence / standpoint collapse to a flat schema:organizer edge; the page's other isAbout mentions drop; only the principal subject becomes mainEntity, with its inverse mainEntityOfPage on the subject; the page→site mereology is the breadcrumb hierarchy; schema:BreadcrumbList's ordered ListItem wrapper is a presentation concern over this isPartOf chain (P12); the specialized PURRDF parthood subproperty, if any, is collapsed to generic schema:isPartOf; the PaymentMethod individual collapses to its label text; schema:paymentAccepted is a free-text list; the Participation's period / confidence / evidence / standpoint collapse to a flat schema:performer edge; namePurpose (endonym/exonym/superseded) is ignored; every displayable name is emitted as schema:name. The consumer receives all co-equal claims without privileging.; exonym selection is locale-relative; precise coordinates coarsened to the enclosing region at purrdf:coarsenTo level (privacy generalization, P10); competing-standpoint names and names with specific purposes dropped; projection frame = endonym-preferred; co-equal exonyms projected as schema:alternateName; non-displayable/superseded and competing-standpoint names dropped; the Post (seat ⟂ holder) and Membership relator collapse to a flat schema:roleName; contested membership claims are not distinguished; the WebPage→ProfilePage refinement is the defined-class inference (page principally about an Agent); schema gets the bare ProfilePage typing; schema:programmingLanguage points at the first-class language (itself projected to schema:ComputerLanguage by mapSchemaProgrammingLanguage); only the project→language edge is carried, not the language's sociolinguistic detail; the quoted source is typed schema:Quotation and linked by schema:citation; the inline quoted text (purrdf:quotedText), when present, rides as schema:text on the Quotation via mapSchemaQuotedText; the inline quoted text lands on the Quotation node (the reused source); its position/offset within the quoting work is not modelled; the typed stepOutput collapses to a flat schema:result edge; PURRDF Route is domain-generic; schema:Trip is travel-specific. RouteKind, start, end, and via metadata are dropped.; the service offering is typed schema:Service; the serviceType value collapses to its label; the SkillProficiency relator (level, scale, interval, standpoint, confidence) collapses to a flat schema:knowsAbout edge; the open posting-kind value collapses to schema's fixed SocialMediaPosting class; the repository facet narrows to schema's source-code reading; clone protocol detail drops; the inverse reading: the parent gains schema:subOrganization pointing at each child; the inverse reading: the topic gains subjectOf pointing back at the work; the typed stepInput collapses to a flat schema:supply edge; tagger, scheme, interval, confidence, provenance dropped; only tag label survives; only tax-scheme identifiers are emitted; other schemes are carried by their own cells; the typed stepInput collapses to a flat schema:tool edge when the input is a physical object; the version-lineage edge coarsens to schema:hasPart (the version is part of the lineage's release set); the lineage semantics drop.
PREFIX purrdf: <https://blackcatinformatics.ca/purrdf/>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>
PREFIX skos: <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#>
PREFIX schema: <https://schema.org/>

CONSTRUCT {
    ?absWork schema:abstract ?absText .
    ?place schema:accessibilityFeature ?featureFacet .
    ?place schema:accessibilityHazard ?hazardFacet .
    ?ent schema:acquireLicensePage ?alp .
    ?exec a schema:Action .
    ?holder schema:address ?addr .
    ?addr a schema:PostalAddress .
    ?addr schema:streetAddress ?street .
    ?addr schema:addressLocality ?locality .
    ?addr schema:addressRegion ?region .
    ?addr schema:postalCode ?pcode .
    ?addr schema:addressCountry ?ccode .
